QUALIFICATION: derivation is probably from the Latin longus = long + manus = hand, referring to the long pectoral fin and could be regarded as a noun in apposition; however the name was treated as an adjective by Cuvier (1831), possibly believing the derivation was from the Greek manos = wide or in some cases manus with a prefix can become an adjective indicating handed, which is followed here with the genus feminine
